Rafał Trzaskowski, Mayor of Warsaw since 2018, has introduced several initiatives benefiting residents. Free nurseries for 14,500 children ease family costs. Metro expansion with six new stations and eco-friendly buses improve commuting. Healthcare access grew with the Southern Hospital and free vaccines. However, projects like the 120 million złoty pedestrian bridge faced criticism for high costs, and tram delays sparked resident frustration. While 64% of Warsaw residents rate his governance positively, some criticize perceived political ambitions and costly cultural projects like the Museum of Modern Art.
